Scope: Items usable by Strike ships. Units: meters (m), m/s, deg/s, deg/s², seconds, currency shown as the UI displays (e.g., 10,000). Durability values are the item’s max at L1.

Global combat/stat rules (for the engine to use consistently)

Hit chance: hit_chance = clamp01( (AttackerAccuracy - DefenderAvoidance) / accuracy_scale )
– Use your game’s accuracy_scale (e.g., 400 = baseline). Negative values clamp to 0.
– Avoidance comes from the ship + modules (e.g., Light RCS Ducting +15).

Armor & AP: EffectiveArmor = max(0, Armor - ArmorPiercing);
DamageTaken = RawDamage * (1 - EffectiveArmor/100) (clamped ≥ 0).

Criticals: On hit, compute crit using attacker’s Critical Offense vs defender’s Critical Defense (already defined in your combat model).

Firing arc: Degrees the hardpoint can legally fire within (don’t roll the mount beyond this).

Reload: Cooldown between shots.

Power cost: Energy removed from the ship per shot/activation.

Upgrade axes: For the L1 items below, note which fields upgrade. If not listed as “(upgrades)”, keep the value constant across levels unless you later capture higher-level screenshots.

